title: ootsuki_makoto
body:
The young man who confesses his love to Mikoto. 16 years old.

[spoiler]Much more unhinged than he initially appears with a very twisted view of romance. States that he likes her most when she is hating him, and would actually prefer that she not develop romantic feelings for him.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Hence the roughly translated title: [i]To The Hateful You, I Like You.[/i][/spoiler]

[spoiler]Why he has become the way he is - that is to say volatile, unpredictable, abusive and [i]irredeemably vulgar[/i] in his expression of 'love' yet oddly sweet to Mikoto -  is assumed to be revealed later throughout the story.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Despite never having had a boyfriend or having been asked out before, she is proud in maintaining her girlfriend status with Makoto to show him off to her friends and is intent on up-keeping appearances despite his [i]abominable[/i] behavior.[/spoiler]

A duffel bag, also known as a gym bag, is a cylindrical [[bag]] carried over the shoulder, made from canvas or similarly rugged materials. It can be closed with a [[drawstring]] or [[zipper]]. title: sg550_(upotte!!)
body:
Personification of the Swiss Arms 550 rifle from the manga and anime [[upotte!!]], almost always addressed as "shiggu." She wears the standard red bow, white shirt and green skirt as the other junior high kids at her school, and has black hair that she keeps in a covered bun. She is a standout member of just about every extra-curricular her school offers, most notably the marksmanship team. She is portrayed as cool, calm, capable and confident. 

She's also intensely arrogant. She's snide and aloof with with everyone- even her "friends", she arrives late to every sports match her team competes in, she harasses her teammates, cheats in competitions, is disrespectful to her opponents, is a sore loser and caustic winner, and bypasses all rules and standards because she views herself as above them.

The author/artist of Upotte (Tennouji Kitsune, better known as "eggplant") is a big fan of the actual SG 550, and his interest bleeds through to the character shiggu. Unfortunately despite being an airsoft and deactivated enthusiast he has no experience and little knowledge on firearms, and his ignorance, like his interest, bleeds through to his work and expecially the character of SG, who gains exaggerated skills from Eggplant's perception of the real SG. Most notable is SG's sniping talents; the real SIG550 utilizes a special cartridge which gives it increased long-range abilities; Eggplant, uninformed about the specifics of the cartridge, gave SIG a MOA of around .2 and an effective range of around two miles- both drastically inflated from the truth.

SG's sour personality, exaggerated skills and the author's exaggerations have earned her the adoration of some but the hatred of most, and she's collected many nicknames, such as "deus ex shiggu", "marry shiggu" "ugly and unworthy" "Shoddy and Gawdy #550" and others.

An extremely common misconception among Upotte fans and gun enthusiast is that the SG 550, and therefore shiggu, Is made by Sig Sauer. This is untrue. Sig Sauer only makes the 556, an import legal copy- the "SIG" part of SIG SG 550 stands for "Schweizerische Industrie Gesellschaft", the original makers.

They were also known to form massive migrating flocks, consisting of millions or even [i]billions[/i] of birds. The species became extinct through the destruction of their habitat (by mass logging), mass hunting and their own gregariousness (a large population was necessary to sustain the species). title: a7m_reppuu
body:
The [b]Mitsubishi A7M Reppuu[/b] (烈風, "Strong Gale") was a carrier-based fighter intended to be the successor to the legendary [[A6M Zero]]. Like its predecessor, it was designed by [[Horikoshi Jirou]]. While superior in every aspect to the Zero, a combination of the design team being diverted to other projects, earthquake damage and bombing raids on the Mitsubishi factory prevented it from ever going into mass production; ultimately only 9 examples were made and none saw combat. It's Allied reporting name was [b]"Sam"[/b].

Ace pilot [[Sakai Saburou]], who was a test pilot for the Reppuu, said that it could literally fly circles around a [[P-51 Mustang]] or [[F6F Hellcat]], even while climbing.

title: lando_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character introduced in the [[Fire Emblem Cipher]] trading card game. Known as [b]Randal[/b] in the Western localizations.

Class: [b]Cavalier[/b] -> Paladin/Great Knight

Lando is a laid-back warrior with a gambling streak, always carrying a dice with him to battle, but is also a skilled swordsman who [[dual_wielding|dual-wields]] swords on horseback. Lando is the fourth character introduced in (and currently exclusive to) Cipher, and the first male of the bunch, after [[emma_(fire_emblem)|Emma]], [[shade_(fire_emblem)|Shade]] and [[yuzu_(fire_emblem)|Yuzu]].

Lando's appearance in Set 7 implies that he was at the very least morally ambiguous, if not an outright villain, given his smug disposition and scoffing at things such as a knight's honor. His earlier appearance, where he is 20 years older, shows him with the gambling behavior mentioned above.

body:

Characters in this situation tend to express delight that borders on sexual fulfillment, usually resulting in lots of blushing, salivating and sometimes even [[happy tears|crying for joy]]. A portmanteau of [[food]] + [[orgasm]].

title: tokio_(time_bokan)
body: [b]Tokio[/b] is a middle school-aged boy from the year 2016. Due to his constant tardiness and slowness, he is so loose with the concept of time that he is somehow able to synchronize perfectly with the [[Mekabuton]]'s ability to "Time Bokan", i.e. travel through time with little complications. He becomes a member of the JKK and is partnered with the already initiated member [[calen_(time_bokan)|Calen]] to travel through time and collect True History gems.

title: takada_gan
body: Takada Gan is a 13-year-old boy whose father is a famous toy designer who failed to complete the "[[Yatter-Wan]]", a dog-shaped all-terrain rescue robot. His weapon of choice is a [[kendama]], which he uses as a flail and grappling hook as well as for his special attack "Kenda-Magic".

title: yassai_mossai
body:
Yassai Mossai (Sokonoke Sokonoke) is the local dance of Kisarazu city of the Chiba prefecture.


h4. [[Senki Zesshou Symphogear]]

From [1]: 
'In the second OVA when Hibiki explains to Miku about the mission she and Chris are doing, we see thought bubbles with Chris shouting "Yassai Mossai" repeatedly, and later "Chossai" ...'

'... "Yassai Mossai":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qn_rI7qGEt4] is the name of the representative dance of Kisarazu city in Chiba prefecture, Japan. Chris was taught this dance by her parents when she was young (there’s a picture of this in the manga!). “Yassai Mossai” are really just lyrics created to fit the song, but they do carry the meaning of “Get out of the way! Get out of the way!‘ 

'Chris’s other phrase, "Chossei” (ちょっせぇ) is a shortened version of “Chorokusai” (ちょろくさい) which in turn was a mix of the phrases “Choroi” and “Kusai.” It carries various meanings depending on the context, but it’s intended to be insulting. When directed at a person it can be “weak,” “dumb,” or “slow.” When referring to a task it can mean “ too easy” or “no big deal.".'

title: flakpanzer_iv_moebelwagen
body:
The 3.7 cm Flak auf Fahrgestell Panzerkampfwagen IV (sf) (Sd.Kfz. 161/3), nicknamed Möbelwagen ("Moving Van") because of its boxy shape, was a self-propelled anti-aircraft gun built from the chassis of the Panzer IV tank. It was used by the Wehrmacht in the European Theatre of World War II.

In 1943, due to the waning ability of the Luftwaffe to combat enemy ground-attack aircraft, ground-based anti-aircraft weaponry was becoming increasingly important to the Wehrmacht. In early 1943, the idea of creating a gun platform on the chassis of the Panzer IV was first proposed. The prototype displayed to Hitler on December 7, 1943, used the 2 cm Flakvierling 38, which was deemed too weak for the latest aircraft, which were constantly being improved to fly higher and faster. Only a single prototype with this gun was produced before the design was rejected. A second design with an upgraded single 3.7 cm Flak 43 L/89 was approved as a temporary stopgap until better Flakpanzers could be created. 240 Möbelwagens were built, and the first production models were put into service on the Western Front in April 1944.

title: ki-27
body:
The [b]Nakajima Ki-27[/b] was a Japanese fighter aircraft during the Second World War. The Japanese Army designation was "[b]Army Type 97 Fighter[/b]" (九七式戦闘機). Its Allied reporting name was [b]Nate[/b].

It was noted for its outstanding turning ability due to its low wing loading, and fixed landing gear. This came at the expense of speed, protection (lacking self-sealing fuel tanks and armour for the pilot) and armament. It was armed with two 7.7 x 58 mm Type 89 machine guns or one 7.7 x 58 mm Type 89 machine gun and one 12.7 x 81 mm Ho-103 machine gun, both of which were inadequate against Allied aircraft.

It was designed by Koyama Yasushi [小山 悌] who would subsequently design the [[Ki-84 Hayate]]. It entered combat for first time in 1937. The Mansyuu Ki-79 was a trainer version.

A [[Russo-Japanese War]]~[[Wolrd War I]] era armored [[cruiser]] of [[Imperial Japanese Navy]]. She was originally built as an Argentine Giuseppe Garibaldi-class cruiser. Her sister ship was [[nisshin_(cruiser)|Nishhin]].
She was sunk in "an air raid at Yokosuka":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_Yokosuka] in July, 1945 as a training vessel.

title: overlord_(transformers)
body:
A name that appeared in the [[Transformers]] franchise/multiverse. The most known one is from the [[Transformers Super-God Masterforce]].

[b]Overlord[/b] is an evil [[Decepticon]], a sentient [[alien]] [[robot]] that can separate into a powerful giant [[cybertron]]ian [[tank]] and a large cybertronian jet, or transform into a military attack base and also a giant aircraft.

Motto: [i]"I stand my ground. I accept any challenge. I am hungry for conflict....!!!".[/i]

Not to be confused with [[Overload (Transformers)]].
